		<div class="comment-body"><p>i think it comes from lots of effort on their end. &#8220;Thin and lean&#8221; comes from doing yoga, swimming, diet and lots of sports (at least 4 times a week in the gym). &#8220;Perfect hair&#8221; comes from perfect and expensive hairdresser. when i do my color and hair lamination for the next 2 weeks i look like fairy with pony tail in sweatshirt. But every time i go to hairdresser i spend min of 150 euro :( which is monthly&#8230; Same goes with &#8220;perfect skin&#8221;.  Walking in heels &#8211; ah yeah.. there is a trick here: super expensive footwear; not talking about crazy shoes but sky-high Louboutins are actually pretty easy to walk in.<br />
Expensive clothes IS expensive clothes. Rare moments of true second-hand or vintage are always minimized and polished with Chanel 2.55 or it-shoes.<br />
And they DO have cellulite :) Just remember Kate Moss in recent LV cat walk &#8211; they just know how to hide it.<br />
What i learned about being smooth is that you have to be very forward with your beauty routine (and spend lots on it) plus use the help of professionals. and invest in some key designer pieces of your wardrobe (i choose shoes, bags and leather coat/jacket). But it pays off when you want to look smooth&#8230;</p>
</div>

