		<div class="comment-body"><p>Lusi, they don&#8217;t spend 300 euros per day either! You&#8217;re talking about socialités, princesses, rich girls from the Upper East Side or daughters of Oil Emperors of the Middle East, these are not the women I&#8217;m talking about!</p>
<p>Those girls, those I don&#8217;t like them too and I would never like to be like them.</p>
<p>The ones that I&#8217;m talking about are women that are hard workers (and their money come from their hard work and nothing else than that) and surely don&#8217;t have the time to spend in beauty farms (maybe they go to the gym, but a hour three times a week is not that hard to find, especially if you don&#8217;t have children). I would really like you to know some of the ones I know, because I&#8217;m sure it&#8217;s the only way to make you understand what I mean ;-)</p>
<p>I do admire people of courage, creativity and freedom of thought (my biggest myths are surely not Taylor Tomasi Hill or Anna Wintour) but in my frivolous world, which is 5% of my whole world but still exists, made of diets, care of my body, gym, nail polish and nice clothes I do admire also the women that  have the time to have great careers, a family and still find the time to look polished and beautiful. Some of them don&#8217;t even know what a primer is, they don&#8217;t know who Shu Uemura is and surely they don&#8217;t spend as much as I do in make-up but they&#8217;re still able to look like that because they have simple but powerful characteristics that make them much more polished than I do with the triple of the effort.<br />
This is what I wanted to point out in my post and what I&#8217;m trying to explain you.</p>
<p>Then, there are many kinds of smoothness. For some it is the sexy curvy woman that does Burlesque (that actually I like very much too) , for me is this one. I do respect and like any kind of beauty, but I don&#8217;t like laziness, I don&#8217;t like people who say (me included, most of the times) &#8220;I don&#8217;t have time for this&#8221; or &#8220;I don&#8217;t even try it because I&#8217;ll never look as I&#8217;d like to&#8221;. I do respect who doesn&#8217;t want to be like that (some of my best friends in primis) but not who doesn&#8217;t try to be as they&#8217;d like to and maybe also spend the day complaining.</p>
<p>I know we&#8217;ll never think the same but I&#8217;d just like to make you understand what I think and what I was talking about :-)</p>
